org.grouplens.lenskit.vectors.similarity

Class SignificanceWeightedVectorSimilarity

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.grouplens.lenskit.vectors.similarity.SignificanceWeightedVectorSimilarity
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, VectorSimilarity

    @Shareable
public class SignificanceWeightedVectorSimilarity
extends Object
implements VectorSimilarity, Serializable

    Apply significance weighting to a similarity function. The threshold is configured with the SigWeightThreshold parameter.

    Significance weighting decreases the similarity between two vectors when the number of common entities between the two vectors is low. For a threshold (S) and key sets (K_1) and (K_2), the similarity is multipled by [\frac{|K_1 \cap K_2|}{\mathrm{max}(|K_1 \cap K_2|, S)}]

    • Herlocker, J., Konstan, J.A., and Riedl, J. An Empirical Analysis of Design Choices in Neighborhood-Based Collaborative Filtering Algorithms. Information Retrieval Vol. 5 Issue 4 (October 2002), pp. 287-310.
    See Also:
    SigWeightThreshold, Serialized Form
